</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umazzil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mazzil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Chieftess<br>Warrior Priestess</span><br>  Posts: 780<br> <font color=#660000>(8/21/02 12:19:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=261.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tidbits of Trivia   ((open to everyone))</span><hr size=1> Picking up the cards from the table, Nullo leans back in her chair and begins to shuffle them.  &quot;Oh?&quot;  Another Freeport raised elf, eh?  She laughs a little.  &quot;Well, I suppose that does make a bit of sense.  No wonder I get along so well with you.&quot;<br>
<br>
She pauses for a moment in her shuffling as she begins to think of something that many of the girls did not know.  Well, there was her lengthy formal name, as opposed to the nickname that she went almost exclusively by now. And those many years spent working the bar in Tassle's Tavern...<br>
<br>
A lazy smile crosses her lips as she reflects upon her foundling years in Freeport.  Suppose that would do, she thought.<br>
<br>
Blue eyes twinkling with a glint of mischief, she looked around the room.  &quot;Did you know how I came by the nickname Nullo?&quot;  Several shrugs spurred her onward.  <br>
<br>
Laughing, she says, &quot;I used to work as a barmaid in Northern Freeport.  I wasn't raised there as Llylewen was, but I've spent enough of my life there to consider it my home.  As for my name...&quot;  She pauses to flash a big grin.  &quot;It was all the drunken humans could manage of my given name when they shouted for their drinks.&quot; <br>
<br>
Shaking her head, she continued.  &quot;Oh no, they couldn't manage a simple, 'Please Nullinea, may I have some more?'  It was always, 'Oi! Null...oh, pash me anudder stoutorwhat!'&quot;<br>
<br>
She finishes her shuffling and begins to deal out a fresh hand of cards.  &quot;And so I was forever named.&quot;<br>
<br>
