<br>
&quot;As many of you know, I was raised in the Temple of Marr in Freeport. It was, for me, my first home, and I did not find peace after leaving it until I found our Sisterhood.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have only told a few of you, however, that I was not born in Freeport. In fact, I was born in the desert of Ro. When I was a child, I was found wandering its northern edges by a patrol of the Freeport Militia. They saved me from death by thirst and starvation, and not knowing what to do for me, they brought me to the Temple of Marr.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is why I have always had a soft spot in my heart for the Militia, whom so many of my order hate. To me, my first memories of the Militia are those strong, heroic guards that took me in out of the desert, and brought me to my home.&quot; <p>Nysa, Priestess of Erolissi<br>
